    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-03-07T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-03-07T05:00:00-05:00" n="174"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d174">
                <head>174. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Israel</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d174fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 684A.85322/3–756. Secret. Received at 10:23 p.m. Repeated to Cairo,
                        Amman, Damascus, Beirut, London, Paris, Ankara, Jerusalem, Baghdad, and
                        Jidda.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-03-07T12:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1956—noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>899. Reference Bnat Yaacov (Embassy telegram 893<note n="2" xml:id="d174fn2">
                        <ref target="#d170">Document 170</ref>.</note>), Foreign Minister requested
                    late last night following additions be made to his comment to me: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Re General <persName corresp="#p_BMGELM1">Burns</persName>, will
                            United States request him to permit <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss>
                            begin work if in course of few weeks Syrians do not agree to <gloss
                                target="#t_JVP1">JVP</gloss>?</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>What would United States do if Israel began work after waiting period
                            brings no results? Will United States in that case inform Syrians “in
                            advance” that United States will support <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                                >GOI</gloss> position?</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>I made no attempt to give categorical replies to either <persName
                        corresp="#p_SM1">Sharett</persName> or <persName corresp="#p_HCC1"
                        >Herzog</persName> his messenger as he obviously expected me to submit
                    questions to Department for reply either through Israeli Embassy or this
                    Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LEB1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Lawson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
